description.narrative: Girls and boys under five years of age, adolescent girls and women during pregnancy and breastfeeding in Somalia have increased and more equitable access to quality preventative nutrition services by 2025, which contributes to Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2025, fewer children, particularly those under the age of 5 years, and women suffer from under-nutrition: stunting, acute malnutrition and micronutrient deficiencies.
